<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Programming note:</strong><em> Money S=
tuff will be off tomorrow, back on Monday.</em></p>
<table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Tether lending</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I know I say this a lot but I really can=E2=80=
=99t stress enough what a good business Tether, the big stablecoin issuer, =
is. It is an=C2=A0<em>unregulated bank that does not pay interest</em>, rat=
es are going up, and its depositor base is quite stable. As of the end of J=
une, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32789269.2904=
22/aHR0cHM6Ly9hc3NldHMuY3RmYXNzZXRzLm5ldC92eXNlODhjZ3dmYmwvNjNvSmVQT0hxSXZy=
Y25YV01QWjFNMC80Y2ZhZjJlN2NkZjgwYzMwYjE3ZmRjNzBmYWFmNzQxZi9FU08uMDMuMDFfU3R=
kX0lTQUVfMzAwMFJfT3Bpbmlvbl8zMC0wNi0yMDIzX0JET19UZXRoZXJfQ1JSLnBkZg/607f07c=
eef4b8524a319a23cBe8378ef6" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" =
target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important=
; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-sty=
le: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Tether reported</a> assets of about $8=
6.5 billion, a majority of it in US Treasury bills, to back about $83.2 bil=
lion of Tethers. That=E2=80=99s up slightly from <a href=3D"https://link.ma=
il.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32789269.290422/aHR0cHM6Ly9hc3NldHMuY3RmYXNz=
ZXRzLm5ldC92eXNlODhjZ3dmYmwvMjRHNER1UTBIRTdoN0VRRTZ2R3k0Si84YThhMTcwZWRmNjg=
3ZWEwN2IzZjg2MDQ4YWY4Yjg3Yi9FU08uMDMuMDFfU3RkX0lTQUVfMzAwMFJfT3Bpbmlvbl8zMS=
0wMy0yMDIzX0JET19UZXRoZXJfQ1JSLnBkZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB2617e2e0" ite=
mprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"colo=
r: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bor=
der-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #c=
cc;"> the previous quarter</a>: In last year=E2=80=99s crypto winter there =
was a <em>bit </em>of a run on Tether, but not that much, and it has recove=
red well; crypto people continue to want to keep their money in Tether.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway, if you are in charge of Tether, you sh=
ouldn=E2=80=99t have to worry about run risk. Tether invests in mostly shor=
t-term safe stuff, and short-term safe stuff pays a lot of interest now.=C2=
=A0Just investing Tether=E2=80=99s pot of money in overnight loans secured =
by US Treasuries at the Secured Overnight Financing Rate would get you a yi=
eld of about 5.3%, or about $4.6 billion a year, absolutely risk-free and w=
ith essentially no expenses.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1=
" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-=
width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !import=
ant; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0If people come in with Tethers looking to get dollars back, you c=
an just give them the dollars; your investments are short-term and liquid. =
Phenomenal business.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">What this means is that if you are in charge o=
f Tether and someone shows up at your office to pitch you on a clever inves=
tment that will get you a higher return with only a little risk, you should=
 put your fingers in your ears and scream =E2=80=9CNO=E2=80=9D and kick the=
m out of your office. You can make billions of dollars of pure profit takin=
g=C2=A0<em>no=C2=A0</em>risk! No credit risk (buy Treasuries), no duration =
risk (buy very short-dated Treasuries), no liquidity risk (easily sell your=
 Treasuries if anyone withdraws Tethers), no nothing, 5% interest.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This sort of thing =E2=80=94=C2=A0where to put=
 the money =E2=80=94=C2=A0can be an existential problem for real banks! We =
have <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32789269.2904=
22/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDMtMTAv=
c3RhcnR1cC1iYW5rLWhhZC1hLXN0YXJ0dXAtYmFuay1ydW4_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDkyMTIzX01PTkV=
ZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09Mj=
MwOTIxJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB0723e704" i=
temprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"co=
lor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; b=
order-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: =
#ccc;">  talked about</a> how Silicon Valley Bank needed to take investment=
 risk to make enough money to run its business, so it put money into long-t=
erm Treasuries thinking they were safe, and then there was a run on the ban=
k and SVB collapsed. I feel for them; they had to take risks to make money.=
 Tether does not! Not at all, not a teeny bit; if Tether loaned $100 to App=
le Inc. for a month that would be slightly irrational.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And yet Tether=E2=80=99s disclosed balance she=
et is=C2=A0<em>not</em>, entirely, the safest stuff you can imagine. At the=
 Wall Street Journal, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cl=
ick/32789269.290422/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9maW5hbmNlL2N1cnJlbmNpZXMvdGV=
0aGVyLWlzLWxlbmRpbmctaXRzLXN0YWJsZWNvaW5zLWFnYWluLWIxMTcwNWYyP21vZD1pdHBfd3=
Nq/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBd66495bb" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"i=
temscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none =
!important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-=
bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Jonathan Weil reports</a>:</=
p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Tether Holdings resumed lending out its own st=
ablecoins to customers, less than a year after it said it would wind down t=
he practice.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The cryptocurrency issuer in its latest quarte=
rly financial update said its assets included $5.5 billion of loans as of J=
une 30, up from $5.3 billion a quarter earlier. A company spokeswoman confi=
rmed that Tether made new loans.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The company, which is incorporated in the Brit=
ish Virgin Islands, calls them secured loans and discloses little about the=
 borrowers or the collateral accepted. The loans are issued and denominated=
 in the company=E2=80=99s tether tokens. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The resumption of lending is a shift from Dece=
mber 2022, when the company said it would reduce its secured loans to zero =
during 2023. =E2=80=9CDuring the second quarter of 2023, we received a few =
short-term loan requests from clients with whom we have cultivated longstan=
ding relationships, and we made the decision to accommodate these requests,=
=E2=80=9D Tether Holdings spokeswoman Alex Welch said.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">She said loans would be eliminated by 2024. Sh=
e said the company=E2=80=99s aim =E2=80=9Cis to prevent any significant dep=
letion of our customers=E2=80=99 liquidity or the need for them to sell the=
ir collateral at potentially unfavorable prices, which could result in loss=
es.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Welch declined to explain why the company=E2=
=80=99s customers might have needed to sell their collateral at unfavorable=
 prices, or whether Tether Holdings made new loans this year to help custom=
ers avoid defaulting on existing loans.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The point I made above is that there is no fin=
ancial reason for Tether to=C2=A0<em>want=C2=A0</em>these loans. Everyone i=
nvolved in Tether can get dynastically wealthy and live an easy life by put=
ting all the money in Treasury bills.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Tether=E2=80=99s spokeswoman is making the sam=
e point here: Tether isn=E2=80=99t making these loans because=C2=A0<em>it=
=C2=A0</em>wants to, because it thinks they are a good financial decision f=
or Tether. Tether is making these loans to=C2=A0<em>support its borrowers</=
em>. Somebody out there =E2=80=94=C2=A0crypto exchanges or trading firms, e=
tc. =E2=80=94=C2=A0has some collateral (presumably volatile cryptocurrencie=
s) and wants to borrow dollars (in the form of Tethers), and Tether Holding=
s is the cheapest and most available lender they can find. Somebody in cryp=
to needs money to buy (or keep holding onto) their crypto, and Tether will =
provide the money, secured by the crypto, not because that=E2=80=99s a good=
 deal for Tether but because Tether is being a good citizen of the crypto e=
cosystem and supporting its counterparties.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Tether=E2=80=99s borrowers are big crypto inve=
stors looking to get financing for their crypto collateral, and if they ran=
 out of liquidity they would need =E2=80=9Cto sell their collateral at pote=
ntially unfavorable prices, which could result in losses.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0If =
big crypto firms get margin calls and have to dump their assets, that will =
drive down the prices of crypto assets. Lending them money is not just good=
 for them, it=E2=80=99s good for the crypto ecosystem broadly: It prevents =
fire sales that might drive down prices.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We have <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/32789269.290422/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGlu=
aW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTItMDEvc2JmLW1pc3NlZC1mdHgtcy1yaXNrcz9jbXBpZD1CQkQ=
wOTIxMjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlci=
Z1dG1fdGVybT0yMzA5MjEmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a=
23cB067d60fb" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bla=
nk" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-botto=
m-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; bac=
kground-color: #ccc;">  talked about</a> Tether=E2=80=99s lending activity =
before. One common form of crypto-skeptical conspiracy theory in recent yea=
rs goes something like this: =E2=80=9CTether is a form of self-sustaining f=
ractional reserve banking for crypto, and it dynamically prints Tethers in =
order to prop up crypto prices. At the margin, cryptocurrencies are not pur=
chased by real people putting new dollars into the crypto system, but by cr=
ypto hedge funds buying crypto using freshly printed Tethers.=E2=80=9D=C2=
=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is =E2=80=A6=C2=A0kind of =E2=80=A6 a Tet=
her spokeswoman =E2=80=A6=C2=A0saying =E2=80=A6=C2=A0that?=C2=A0</p>
