<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One way to think about crypto is that it often=
 applies infinitely scalable technology to ideas that kind of only work onc=
e. So in the early days of Bitcoin, a lot of people, including me, thought =
there was a logical flaw at its heart: Bitcoin was just a ledger maintained=
 by some open-source code, and if it ever got valuable there was nothing to=
 stop anyone else from cloning it and printing many more quasi-Bitcoins tha=
t had the same properties and, therefore, the same value as actual Bitcoins=
. This easy clonability would keep a lid on Bitcoin prices. This was totall=
y wrong! In fact a lot of people=C2=A0<em>did=C2=A0</em>make Bitcoin clones=
, and a few of them ended up being worth, you know, two or three orders of =
magnitude less than Bitcoin, and the rest ended up being worth nothing. The=
re were powerful network effects to being the original thing, and while it =
was easy to copy the technical properties of that thing, the value was not =
in the technical properties.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Non-fungible tokens have a similar story, but =
much more so. I do not fully understand the appeal of, like, Bored Ape Yach=
t Club. But it=E2=80=99s something like:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">There is a limited collection of digi=
tal images of apes, each of which is associated with a numbered crypto toke=
n.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You can buy one of the numbered=
 tokens and then you =E2=80=9Cown,=E2=80=9D in some not-really-worth-thinki=
ng-about way, the associated image of an ape.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bo=
ttom: 5px;">You can use the ape as your Twitter profile picture,<a class=3D=
"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-5" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorat=
ion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00000=
0; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !imp=
ortant; display: inline-block;">
<span>[5]</span>
</a>=C2=A0and other people who also =E2=80=9Cown=E2=80=9D apes can see your=
 profile picture and be like =E2=80=9Cooh, you own an ape too, cool cool.=
=E2=80=9D</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Of course anyone can use=
 the ape as their Twitter profile picture =E2=80=94=C2=A0buying the token a=
nd downloading the digital image are entirely separate transactions =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0but to the people in the club=C2=A0<em>those=C2=A0</em>people will=
 look like phonies and poseurs; to be in the club you need not just the pic=
ture but the token.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Maybe also you=
 like the picture of the ape? You like the aesthetic? It=E2=80=99s like buy=
ing a cool article of clothing or bag or whatever; you feel good wearing it=
 (as your Twitter profile picture) and other people in the know also think =
you are cool.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The club can have re=
al-life meetups or whatever, where owning the token is your admissions tick=
et.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Also other people might want t=
hese benefits, the supply of apes is limited, and maybe you can buy an ape =
and then sell it to someone else for more money and get rich quick.</li>=09=
<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Celebrities and influencers can be entice=
d into this whole thing, and if they go on TV saying =E2=80=9CI own a Bored=
 Ape and I love it, look how bored it is=E2=80=9D maybe the price of your a=
pe will go up.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Etc.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It=E2=80=99s a combination of quasi-art collec=
tion and quasi-club membership and very 2021 crypto price speculation.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When I put it like that I feel like:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Maybe it=E2=80=99s plausible? Not my t=
hing, exactly, but I can see how someone might want this set of features.</=
li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If it=E2=80=99s plausible, it=E2=80=
=99s plausible=C2=A0<em>more than once</em>. Some people might appreciate t=
he aesthetics of the pictures of apes, and want to be in a club with the ot=
her ape people; other people might prefer the aesthetics of pictures of cat=
s, and want to be in a club with other cat people.</li>=09<li style=3D"marg=
in-bottom: 5px;">It=E2=80=99s not plausible=C2=A0<em>that </em>many times? =
Like you might want to be in a club, or two clubs, or three clubs, and I mi=
ght want to be in a different club from the clubs you are in. But only so m=
any people want to be in crypto-y clubs at all, and if you do, you probably=
 want to be in clubs that other people are in; there are network effects, a=
nd only so many clubs can be valuable and desirable. The mechanics of how s=
ome NFT clubs become cool and others don=E2=80=99t are mysterious to me, bu=
t some such mechanics have to exist.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px=
;">It is trivially easy and free to create new clubs =E2=80=94=C2=A0to make=
 a new NFT collection, generate 10,000 ugly images and sell them online =E2=
=80=94=C2=A0and for a while everyone did.=C2=A0</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-=
bottom: 5px;">At the very peak of the bubble, people would speculate on any=
 of those (you never know which will take off!), but 99% of them will go no=
where.</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway here is a very funny <a href=3D"https:/=
/link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32789269.290422/aHR0cHM6Ly9tYXJrZXRz=
LmJ1c2luZXNzaW5zaWRlci5jb20vbmV3cy9jdXJyZW5jaWVzL25mdC1tYXJrZXQtY3J5cHRvLWR=
pZ2l0YWwtYXNzZXRzLWludmVzdG9ycy1tZXNzYXJpLW1haW5uZXQtY3VycmVuY3ktdG9rZW5zLT=
IwMjMtOQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB3d2b1165" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscop=
e=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration:=
 none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; b=
order-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> report on the state of=
 NFTs</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A report by dappGambl based on data provided b=
y NFT Scan and CoinMarketCap indicated that 95% of non-fungible tokens were=
 effectively worthless. Out of 73,257 NFT collections, 69,795 of them had a=
 market cap of zero ether. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">"This daunting reality should serve as a sober=
ing check on the euphoria that has often surrounded the NFT space," the res=
earchers said. "Amid stories of digital art pieces selling for millions and=
 overnight success stories, it is easy to overlook the fact that the market=
 is fraught with pitfalls and potential losses.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">"It becomes clear that a significant portion o=
f the NFT market is characterized by speculative and hopeful pricing strate=
gies that are far removed from the actual trading history of these assets,"=
 the researchers said.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">They=E2=80=99re not assets! They=E2=80=99re a =
joke that was funny once, twice, maybe a thousand times, but good lord not =
73,000 times, come on.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/32789269.290422/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL=
2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDktMTkvZmFzdGVyLW9wdGlvbnMtYXJlLW1vcmUtZnVuP2NtcGlkPUJC=
RDA5MjEyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGV=
yJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDkyMSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a31=
9a23cD69f8064f" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_b=
lank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bot=
tom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; b=
ackground-color: #ccc;">  talked the other day</a> about the modern history=
 of art pranks, art that was designed not to look pretty but to convey that=
 a collector was cool and in on the joke. I wrote:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And then non-fungible tokens were =
invented to sort of mass-produce this effect for the internet age. <em>This=
 should not work:</em> Pretty pictures lost their edge in the art world bec=
ause they became too easy to mass-produce, and now being-in-on-a-dumb-stunt=
 has also become easy to mass-produce, and it too has, I think, lost its ed=
ge. For like seven minutes in 2021, you could say =E2=80=9Cgive me money an=
d I will give you a receipt for nothing" and people would be like =E2=80=9C=
oh that=E2=80=99s a cool joke, here=E2=80=99s the money=E2=80=9D and feel g=
ood and sophisticated, but that was very easy to do, so everyone did, so th=
at market was saturated and it is, I insist, no longer cool.</p></blockquot=
e>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So saturated! So not cool.</p>
